      {
        "question": "Is periodontal treatment painful?",
        "answer": "Most procedures are performed with local anesthesia to ensure your comfort. Any post-treatment discomfort is typically mild and manageable with over-the-counter pain medication."
      },
      {
        "question": "How long does treatment take?",
        "answer": "Treatment duration varies depending on the condition and procedure. Initial therapy may take 2-4 visits, while maintenance visits are typically scheduled every 3-4 months."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can gum disease be cured?",
        "answer": "While early-stage gum disease can be reversed, advanced periodontitis requires ongoing management. With proper treatment and maintenance, the condition can be effectively controlled."
      },
      {
        "question": "How often should I have periodontal maintenance?",
        "answer": "Most patients benefit from maintenance visits every 3-4 months, though this may vary based on individual needs and risk factors."
      }
